
🚀 Job Finder API Documentation
Welcome! This guide provides all the necessary information to integrate with the Backend services.

Base URL: http://localhost:8080/api/jobs

Content-Type: application/json


1. Sync Jobs (Scraping)
Triggers the background process to scrape jobs from external sources.

Endpoint: /sync

Method: POST

Params: - keyword (String): e.g., "Java", "React".

Success Response (202 Accepted):

JSON
{
  "status": "Processing",
  "message": "Scraping started in the background...",
  "timestamp": "2026-02-15T..."
}



2. Get All Jobs (With Cursor Pagination)
Fetch all jobs using high-performance cursor-based pagination.

Endpoint: /

Method: GET

Params:

lastId (Long/Optional): The ID of the last visible job.

size (int/Default: 10): Number of items per page.

Success Response:

JSON
{
  "data": [
    {
      "title": "Software Engineer",
      "companyName": "Tech Co",
      "location": "Cairo",
      "link": "https://...",
      "companyLogo": "https://..."
    }
  ],
  "pageSize": 10,
  "nextCursor": 864,
  "hasNext": true
}
Note: Use nextCursor value as the lastId for the next request.

3. Search Jobs
Endpoint: /search

Method: GET

Params:

title (String): Search keyword for job titles.

lastId & size: Same as pagination.

4. Error Handling
The API returns a consistent error format for all business exceptions.

Format:
JSON
{
  "errorCode": "ERR_101",
  "message": "Job not found",
  "timestamp": "2026-02-15T...",
  "path": "/api/jobs/search"
}